                </addressee>
                <date when="1884-04-02">31 March 1884</date> &#x2022; <name type="place">Washington, D.C.</name>
                <sourceline>(MS: CU-MARK, UCLC 41996)</sourceline>
            </head>
            <div1 type="letter" xml:id="lt0001">
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Clemmens&#x2014;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p rend="text-indent:3">I have had many applications from friends desiring autographs of distinguished authors; and as yours is one so often begged for, I think I ought to keep quite a store on hand.</p> 
                <p rend="text-indent:2">Will you then kindly send me at once, a dozen or so (with your nom de plume as well)?
                </p>
                <p rend="text-indent:2">When these are exhausted I shall forthwith notify you that I may receive a fresh supply.</p>
                <p rend="text-indent:2">Knowing your reputation for amiability I shall feel no hesitation in asking this slight favor. </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute rend="indentcompclose">Very cordially yours </salute>
                    <signed rend="indentsig">Virginia Waring.</signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>2009 J. st.<lb/><space extent="2"/>Washington<lb/><space extent="8"/>D.C.<lb/>
                    <date when="1884-04-01">April 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> 1884.</date>
                </dateline>
            </div1>
